From 8523fde68cc955eba17089eff027e44f5f4140af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 11:56:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH v2 1/2] Input: stmfts - poll for chip ready in
 stmfts5_configure

stmfts_reset's fixed 50 ms post-deassert delay is sufficient for FTS4
but too short for FTS5: on FTM5 (FTM5CU56AA1BE on Pixel 4a, chip ID
0x4836) firmware boot includes internal CRC verification of code+config
flash sections and can take several hundred milliseconds before the
chip's I2C state machine begins ACKing.  With the existing 50 ms wait
stmfts5_configure's i2c_smbus_read_i2c_block_data() returned -ENXIO,
probe aborted with no useful dmesg (only the dev_dbg "initializing..."
line), and the device stayed in reset.

Rather than extending stmfts_reset()'s sleep to the worst-case duration
(which would penalise every probe), poll i2c_smbus_read until the chip
ACKs.  Average case is unchanged: chip ready -> first read succeeds ->
no extra delay.  Slow case is bounded by 20 * 25 ms = 500 ms.

Diagnosed via ftrace function_graph with funcgraph-retval, which showed
the failing __i2c_transfer returning -6 directly; dmesg surfaced no
error of its own.  Approach inspired by map220v's downstream sm7125
driver which similarly reads chip state during the boot wait rather
than blocking on a fixed sleep.

Signed-off-by: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>
---
 drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c | 20 +++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
index e613299e3..50a6de70e 100644
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
@@ -911,12 +911,22 @@ static int stmfts_power_on(struct stmfts_data *sdata)
 static int stmfts5_configure(struct stmfts_data *sdata)
 {
 	u8 event[STMFTS_EVENT_SIZE];
-	int ret;
+	int ret, retries;
 
-	/* Verify I2C communication */
-	ret = i2c_smbus_read_i2c_block_data(sdata->client,
-					    STMFTS_READ_ALL_EVENT,
-					    sizeof(event), event);
+	/*
+	 * Poll until the chip ACKs an I2C read after reset.  FTS5 firmware
+	 * boot, including any flash CRC verification, can take a few hundred
+	 * ms on FTM5; a fixed post-reset sleep large enough to cover the
+	 * worst case would penalise every probe.  Retry up to ~500 ms.
+	 */
+	for (retries = 0; retries < 20; retries++) {
+		ret = i2c_smbus_read_i2c_block_data(sdata->client,
+						    STMFTS_READ_ALL_EVENT,
+						    sizeof(event), event);
+		if (ret >= 0)
+			break;
+		msleep(25);
+	}
 	if (ret < 0)
 		return ret;
 
